        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 2:49AM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 249 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ferrelview, or near Smithville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kansas City, Liberty, Gladstone, Excelsior Springs, Smithville,
Kearney, Sugar Creek, Riverside, Lawson, Claycomo, Pleasant Valley,
Lake Waukomis, Glenaire, Holt, Oakview, Crystal Lakes, Sibley,
Northmoor, Missouri City, and Houston Lake.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 in Missouri between mile markers 8 and 33.
Interstate 29 between mile markers 1 and 5.
Interstate 635 between mile markers 11 and 12.
Interstate 435 between mile markers 37 and 54.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
